Privacy Policy for Idol Prank Video Call & Chat
Introduction
At LightCode Solutions,
we respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal data. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and share your data when you use our Idol Prank Video Call & Chat application. By using the App, you consent to our processing of your data as set forth in this Privacy Policy.
What Data Do We Collect?
When you use Idol Prank Video Call & Chat application, we collect two types of data.
Automatically Collected Data:
The App collects certain data automatically, such as:
Device type and identifiers (e.g., advertising ID)
IP address and geographical location
Operating system and browser type
Wi-Fi MAC address and data connection status
App usage data and other non-personal data
User Provided Data:
We collect data you provide when you:
Download and use the App
Register for an account (e.g., name, email address, age, username, password)
Make purchases or respond to offers
Contact us for help
Enter data into our application (e.g., contact data)
Data Sharing and Advertising
We use your data in an anonymized, hashed, or obfuscated way to:
Provide our services
Share with third-party advertising networks and analytics companies for targeted advertising
Share with our trusted service providers who work on our behalf
Disclose as required by law or to protect our rights and safety
We do not pass personally identifiable data to ad networks or advertisers. You can opt out of targeted advertising by following the instructions in the "Managing Your Data" section.
You may visit below links of our third-party advertising networks and analytics to know more about how they collect and use your data.
Google AdMob
Facebook Audience Network
Google Analytics
Firebase Crashlytics
Managing Your Data
You can:
Uninstall the App to stop data collection.
Deactivate 'Location' in your device's settings to stop precise location data collection.
Opt out of cross-app advertising by changing your advertising identifier or using the settings on your device.
Use the NAI and DAA opt-out tools to manage your choices for participating companies.
For more data about these tools please visit below links
http://networkadvertising.org/choices/
or
https://aboutads.info
Data collection from children
We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13 and for EU residents under the age of 16. If we become aware that a child has provided us with personal information without parental consent, we will delete such information. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us at
tannerbrookstanner@gmail.com
Data Retention and Management
We retain user-provided data for as long as you use our Apps and for a reasonable period thereafter. Automatically collected data is stored for up to 12 months and may be stored in aggregate form afterward. If you want us to delete your user-provided data, please contact us at the provided email, and we will respond in a reasonable time.
Business Transfer
In the event of a merger, acquisition, bankruptcy, or sale of assets, your data may be transferred to the acquiring entity. In such cases, we will ensure that your data is handled in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
Security
We are committed to safeguarding the confidentiality of your personal data and provide physical, electronic, and procedural safeguards to protect the data we process and maintain. However, no security system can prevent all potential security breaches. We use anonymization techniques to limit the use of personally identifiable information as much as possible.
Permissions
To provide the best possible experience, our App requires the following permissions:
android.permission.VIBRATE:
We use this permission to access the device's vibrator to provide haptic feedback, which enhances the overall user experience.
android.permission.FLASHLIGHT:
This permission is used for flashlight effect, which would typically use the camera permission. We use this permission to provide a flashlight feature in our App.
android.permission.MODIFY_AUDIO_SETTINGS:
We use this permission to modify global audio settings, such as adjusting volume levels, to ensure that our App's audio features work seamlessly.
android.permission.INTERNET:
We use this permission to access the internet, which is necessary for online functionality like fetching data and providing updates.
android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE:
We use this permission to access information about networks, enabling us to check if the device is connected to the internet and provide a better user experience.
android.permission.CAMERA:
We use this permission to access the device's camera, which is essential for video calling functionality and other camera-related features.
android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE:
We use this permission to run foreground services, which can be useful for tasks that need to be active while the App is in the foreground, such as video calling.
android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE_MEDIA_PROJECTION:
We use this permission to use a foreground service to capture the screen or project media content, if needed, to provide a better user experience.
android.permission.POST_NOTIFICATIONS:
We use this permission to send notifications to the user, which could be used to inform them about screenshot capturing service use or other important updates.
Your Rights & Choices
As a resident of California, you have the following rights:
Right to Know:
You can inquire about the personal data we collect, use, disclose, and sell. You are entitled to make this request twice a year at no cost. If we are unable to accommodate your request, we will explain the reason.
Right to Opt-Out:
You can choose to opt-out of the "sale" of your personal data, as outlined in the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA). We do not knowingly sell the personal data of individuals under 13 without parental consent, or of those aged 13 to 16 without their own consent. If you do not opt-out, your personal data may be sold as stated in this policy.
Right to Delete:
You may request the deletion of your personal data. We may decline your request if we are required to retain your data for legal compliance or to complete a transaction. If we deny your request, we will provide an explanation.
Right to Non-Discrimination:
You are entitled to be free from discriminatory treatment for exercising your privacy rights.
Residents of the European Economic Area (EEA), the United Kingdom, and other designated countries:
You have the right to access, correct, delete, and restrict the processing of your personal information. You can withdraw your consent for us to collect and process your information at any time.
To exercise these rights, please email us at
tannerbrookstanner@gmail.com
Residents of the United States (excluding California) and other countries:
You can opt-out of personalized advertising by changing your device settings. On Android, enable "Opt out of Ads Personalization" under Settings > Google > Ads.
Changes to This Policy
We have the discretion to update this privacy policy at any time. We will provide notice of significant changes through the App or other means. We also will post a notification on the main page of our App. We encourage Users to frequently check this page for any changes to stay informed about how we are helping to protect the personal information we collect.
Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns, please contact us at
tannerbrookstanner@gmail.com
